The paper focuses on using machine learning techniques to improve the prediction performance of student behavior in MOOCs. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and could also be relevant to the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR) due to the use of clickstream data. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of auto-encoders, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact on instructor feedback and timely intervention, which could be relevant to the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
